This paper focuses on the problem of formation control of multirotor MAVs, which is a prominent topic in the field of robotics. The use of Nonlinear Model Predictive Control (NMPC) and relative sensing framework suggests that this paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with control laws and mathematical models, which are relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The use of optimization techniques and real-time iteration suggests that this paper may also belong to the Mathematical Optimization (cs.MA) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of AI techniques such as formation control, which suggests that it may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with evaluation of results, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
